## 3. Target Audience & Searcher Profile

The searcher is most likely a **renter in transition**: someone relocating for work, starting a new job in an unfamiliar city, or needing temporary housing between a lease end and a permanent move. They may also be a first-time renter encountering a short-term agreement for the first time and unsure what terms are standard versus negotiable. They are in the **comparison-to-decision stage** of the renter journey: they have identified that they need a short-term rental but have not yet signed anything. The specific problem they are solving is: "I have been offered or am about to sign a short-term lease agreement, and I want to understand what it says before I commit." Based on the SERP analysis, they expect a structured, scannable article that walks through the agreement clause by clause, written in plain language, not legal boilerplate.

