*Writing instruction: [CONTENT GAP] Competitor content does not clearly distinguish short-term fixed leases from month-to-month agreements for renters deciding between the two. Cover: a short-term fixed lease has a set end date and no automatic renewal; a month-to-month lease rolls over each month until either party gives notice. For renters with uncertain timelines, month-to-month offers more flexibility but often at a higher per-month cost. For renters who know their exact dates, a short-term fixed lease often has slightly lower pricing and clearer terms. Include the notice requirement difference: short-term fixed leases simply end; month-to-month leases require 30-60 days written notice in most states.*

